    "1643894763b28d5070": {
      "type": "Focus-Text-Image-Right",
      "settings": {
        "our-story-vid": "shopify://shop_images/Cellar-02.jpg",
        "right_video_url": "",
        "Heading_size": "h2",
        "Heading_color": "#aac4d3",
        "title": "IN THE CELLAR",
        "video-sec-content-txt-1": "<p>In the Alvi’s Drift cellar, our winemaking team strongly focuses on preserving the fruit-driven expression of the grapes that go into our award-winning South African wines.</p><p>For this wine, optimally ripe grapes are hand-picked in the cool early morning hours. After crushing, prior to fortification, grapes are left on skinsto allow for the full extraction of crystallised sugar in the dried berries. Thereafter, the wine is matured in small, old oak barrels for 18 months.</p>",
